annotationA: Synaptosomal-associated protein 25kDa (Snap25) is a synaptic target SNARE protein and a component of SNARE protein complexes known to function in neurotransmitter release. Snap25 functions in synaptic transmission in larvae and is essential in adults; Belongs to the SNAP-25 family
annotationB: Protein ROP; May be a component of one of the vesicle trafficking pathways. May interact functionally with Ras2 protein
